<P>
   Picking up on  &UR; George Leonard &LR; 's suggestion for the Packy Awards
_ to be given to the creators of impossible, perilous and
aggravating forms of packaging _  &UR; Sally Alexander  &LR; nominates:
</P>
<P>
   - The Swiss Army Knife and Henckels scissors set, both
bubble-packed. Not only did the edge of the package draw blood, the
added irony (worth at least 4 points) is ``that you need the
product in order to get it out of the package.''
</P>
<P>
   - Capri Sun drink pouches with straws: The ``impossible angle''
on the ``insert here'' dot for straw insertion sends the sharp
point of the straw skittering off the pouch and into your palm (3
points).
</P>
<P>
   - Suitcases, garment bags, purses or tote bags that come
packaged in shrink-wrap and ``then are compulsively bagged in
plastic bags by clerks who cinch the ends with lock-tight knots (1
to 3 points, depending on how much additional paper is added to
give shape to the bag inside the package inside the bag).''
</P>
<P>
   &UR; WHO SAID WHAT &LR;
</P>
<P>
   ``Warm potatoes with black truffles _ earth and sex and death.
Everybody should eat their mashed potatoes this way at least
once.''
</P>
<P>
