didn't know the guy's name or anything else. Then, at a reunion,
the two heard each other swapping war stories, then compared notes
and found that Mr. Hardradth was the man who saved the life of the
other GI, Jim O'Neil, who credits Hardradth with saving his life
and being responsible for his 23 grandchildren. The two plan to get
together at another reunion in July and talk by phone Memorial Day.
