<HEADLINE>
MEMORIZE THESE MEMORABILIA SITES FOR MEMORIAL DAY
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By TOM HOFFARTH  
 c.2000 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ Enough about the ebay boom.
</P>
<P>
   There are some less-publicized hot spots for those seeking a
little less confusion in shopping for unique sports collectibles
for sale or by auction. Such as:
</P>
<P>
   --The Dodgers have given Art of the Game, an L.A.-based fine-art
and sports memorabilia chain, exclusive marketing rights to sell
original wooden seats from Dodger Stadium removed from the dugout
and club levels during the recent renovation.
</P>
<P>
   OnlineAuthentics.com has tagged each seat and registered them in
an online data base. Two Web sites (artofthegame.com and
Dodgerseats.com) are the first place to go to check them out.
</P>
<P>
   --At the site of New York-based Grey Flannel Collectables, Inc.
(www.greyflannel.com), previews of some of the more than 1,200
items that will be in their June 19-20 auction can be gazed upon.
</P>
<P>
   Among the loot: The football Joe Montana threw for his final
touchdown pass, the uniform Madonna wore in the movie ``A League of
Their Own,'' and John Rocker's game-used road jersey from the 1999
World Series.
</P>
<P>
   Later this summer, Grey Flannel will hold a live auction with
two dozen items that'll air on ESPN and ESPN Classic.
</P>
<P>
   --After years of bringing order to the chaos of sports card
collecting with its series of price guides, Beckett Publications'
site (www.beckett.com) has taken a foothold in the sports
collectibles marketplace by offering more than 165,000 items from
the country's top dealers.
</P>
<P>
   --Surfboard collectors have a swell little haven to find
longboards, shortboards and body boards at esurfauction
(www.esurfauction.com).
</P>
<P>
   --A look for specific Sports Illustrated and other media guides
and magazines are often found for sale and auction at Yesteryear
Sports Publications (www.yester.com).
</P>
<P>
   --Limited edition boxes of Wheaties with Cincinnati outfielder
Ken Griffey Jr. sold only in Ohio stores are available online at
the General Mills site (generalmills.com/store/). Price: $9.95. &QL; 
!dtpost!!ital!Tom Hoffarth!dlim!!end!
</P>
</TEXT>
