<HEADLINE>
THIS WEEK'S TV HIGHLIGHTS
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By TOM HOFFARTH  
 c.2000 Los Angeles Daily News  
TODAY 
Let's try welcoming the unofficial start of summer by taking in a
baseball game, OK? There are more than a half-dozen choices. Any
will be acceptable. MLB: Angels at Cleveland, Channel 9, 10:05
a.m.; Oakland at New York, ESPN2, 10 a.m.; Atlanta at Chicago, TBS,
1 p.m.; Houston at Colorado, ESPN, 1 p.m.; St. Louis at Arizona,
ESPN2, 1 p.m.; Detroit at Texas, ESPN, 4 p.m.; New York at Dodgers,
Channel 5, 4:05 p.m. 
TUESDAY 
The Blazers have hung around in the Western Conference finals
longer than Andy Richter's farewell week on ``Conan.'' Time to show
these Lakers sidekicks the Staples Center exit, stage left. NBA:
Western Conference finals Game 5: Portland at Lakers, Channel 4, 6
p.m. 
WEDNESDAY 
CBS' much talked-about series ``Survivor'' debuts tonight -- 16
contestants on an island in a survival-of-the-fittest format. Kinda
like the format for the NBA playoffs, except the knicked-up Knicks
refuse to be eaten. !racepay!NBA: Eastern Conference finals, Game
5: New York at Indiana, Channel 4, 6 p.m. 
THURSDAY 
Don't get us started on whether the National Spelling Bee is a
sporting event meant to fill ESPN programming or something
Nickelodeon should be handling right after ``Ren And Stimpy.'' Are
there no more morning exercise shows to plug in instead? Do we have
to see another freckle-faced, red-haired girl spit out words such
as ``logorrhea'' (last year's winning word) as we lose our
cafeteria lunch. Just once, we'd like to hear the big-shot adult
give the word, and have the kid say, ``Hmmmm. Could you spell that
for me?'' National Spelling Bee finals, ESPN, 10 a.m. (replayed on
ESPN2 at 4:30 p.m.) 
FRIDAY 
As this crazy interleague play starts again, it's unfortunate that
Tim Belcher remains on the Angels' disabled list. Get him out there
to pitch again to Chan Ho Park, who desperately wants to defend his
Ultimate Baseball Kickboxing title. MLB: Dodgers at Angels, Channel
5, 7 p.m. (Fox Channel 11 has Saturday's game at 1 p.m. and Fox
Sports Net 2 has Sunday's game at 1 p.m.) 
SATURDAY 
After showing the first two games on cable-friendly ESPN, big
brother ABC takes over the Stanley Cup Finals in Dallas -- and
keeps it the rest of the way. Hockey has never translated into a
network event. Why start now? NHL: Stanley Cup Finals Game 3: New
Jersey at Dallas, Channel 7, 5 p.m. 
SUNDAY 
We thought we told you to get ridda these guys. NBA: Western
Conference finals Game 7: Portland at Lakers, Channel 4, TBA.
