NEW YORK TIMES CORRECTIONS FOR SUNDAY, MAY 28
</HEADLINE>
 Eds.: These corrections will appear in The New York Times on
Sunday. Days and dates refer to the original article's transmission
by the New York Times News Service, and may need to be adjusted by
NYT clients.)  
(ss) 
 c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   BC-CHINA-TRADE-NYT (moved Saturday, May 20)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Saturday, May 20
about the Congressional vote on trade relations with China and its
possible effect on Chinese society referred incorrectly in some
copies to the company where Xu Xiaonian, who commented on the
issue, is a general manager. It is the China International Capital
Corp., not the China Investment Construction Corp.  &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
